# Practice Interview (Mock Interview)

Standalone on-demand feature — **not** in the LangGraph workflow. Conversational practice for a workflow session using the user’s BYOK LLM. English only in v1.

## Product summary

- **Tab:** 9th application-detail tab **Mock Session** (`data-tab="practice"`, `#pane-practice`) — after Interview (Optimize CV sits after Resume)
- **Styles:** `hr` | `pro` | `manager` (required at start)
- **Duration:** `10` | `15` | `20` minutes (default 15) — countdown from server `ends_at`, not fixed round count
- Voice: browser Web Speech API (STT) + `speechSynthesis` (TTS); typed fallback always available
- **Submit UX:** voice auto-submits after ~5s silence (`VOICE_SILENCE_MS`); typing uses **Enter** to send (**Shift+Enter** = newline); **Submit answer** button remains
- **Replay question** / **Mute this question** as quiet session links; **End early** / **Abort** under **More**; **confirm** before End early
- **STAR coach** always on; mid-session **tips** under the answer box (no mid-session topic coverage)
- Debrief includes dimension score explanations in the UI, plus **answer_reviews** (stronger sample per candidate answer, capped at 6) with Copy; legacy `weakest_answer_rewrite` still filled for older clients
- On timer expiry or End early, any draft answer (≥5 chars) is sent as `final_answer` on `POST .../finish` (not a separate `/turn`) so it is included in the debrief transcript
- If End early is clicked while a turn is still in flight, the client **queues** finish, shows scoring UI, and finishes after the turn completes; finish also **retries** on 409 busy
- Mic **pauses while TTS speaks** (avoids capturing interviewer audio)
- While waiting for stream: current-question card shows *Loading…* until the first speak delta
- Ending early / time-up: timer stops immediately and UI shows scoring state until debrief is ready
- Debrief: overall score banner (full summary, no clamp), score breakdown (number on the right of each card), strengths/improvements, stronger sample answers — **no Topics row**, no Copy summary
- Low-time coaching: last question (~2 min), short summary (~1 min), wrap-up (≤30s)
- **No audio upload / no server Whisper** in v1

## Agent

`MockInterviewAgent` in `agents/mock_interview.py`:

| Method | Role |
|--------|------|
| `open_session` | Style pack + job/prep context → first `speak` + plan |
| `next_turn` | Score last answer; `follow_up` / `next_question` / `wrap_up` (force wrap if ≤30s left) |
| `debrief` | Style-weighted scores + strengths / improvements + `answer_reviews` (falls back to transcript shells if LLM omits them) |

Prefer questions from `interview_prep.predicted_questions` when present (HR→behavioral/company; Pro→technical/role; Manager→role/behavioral).

## API (`/api/v1/mock-interview`)

| Method | Path | Notes |
|--------|------|-------|
| `GET` | `/{session_id}` | Active + history |
| `GET` | `/{session_id}/status` | `seconds_remaining`, `is_thinking` |
| `POST` | `/{session_id}/start` | `{style, duration_minutes}` |
| `POST` | `/{session_id}/turn` | `{transcript, source: typed\|stt}` |
| `POST` | `/{session_id}/finish` | Early end + debrief; optional `{final_answer, source}` for unsubmitted draft |
| `POST` | `/{session_id}/abort` | No debrief |

**Guards:** ownership → `require_user_llm_context()` (`CFG_6001`) → rate limit → Redis thinking lock (`set_mock_interview_thinking`).

**Stuck recovery:** `turn` / `finish` accept a stale `status=thinking` only when the Redis lock is **clear**; if the lock is held, return **409**. **Abort** also returns **409** while thinking (never clears another request’s lock).

**Turn parse/filter failure:** agent returns `error`; API broadcasts error and returns **500** without wrapping up or saving — session stays active for retry (same idea as start rejecting bad opens).

**Limits:** 10 starts/hour, 40 turns/hour, 10 finishes/hour; max transcript 4000 chars; min transcript 5 chars; 1 active run per session.

Always `flag_modified(workflow_session, "mock_interview")` on write. Persist via `get_session()` / request `get_database()` with lock cleared in `finally`. Turn/finish/abort mutate a **copy** of `active` and assign back only on successful save. Start rejects open responses with `error` or `act=wrap_up` (parse/filter failures) instead of creating a half-session.

## Storage

JSONB `workflow_sessions.mock_interview` (migration `20260714_0001_026` / revision id `20260714_026`):

```json
{ "version": 1, "active": { ... }, "history": [ /* last 5 completed/aborted */ ] }
```

Score fields from the LLM are clamped with `_safe_score()` (1–10; junk → default 5).

## WebSocket

Reuse `WS /api/v1/ws/workflow/{session_id}`:

- `mock_interview_started`
- `mock_interview_thinking`
- `mock_interview_speak_delta` — progressive `"speak"` text (`data.delta`, `run_id`); TTS not started on deltas
- `mock_interview_utterance` — final speak line; UI TTS still from HTTP response / final speak
- `mock_interview_turn_scored`
- `mock_interview_complete`
- `mock_interview_error`

**Streaming:** `start` / `turn` use `LLMClient.generate_stream` + `SpeakFieldStreamer` (`utils/llm/speak_stream.py`) to extract `"speak"` mid-JSON and broadcast deltas. Debrief stays non-streaming. Stream failure falls back to non-stream `generate()`.

**Client WS guard:** `ui/src/mock-interview/ws-guard.ts` — `isMockInterviewMessageForSession` — ignore events whose `session_id` is not the open application (shared `applypilot:ws` bus).

**Submit UX:** append/clear the answer box only after a **successful** turn HTTP response; on failure restore the last interviewer speak and keep the draft. Clear typing/thinking placeholders when the HTTP success path lands (not only on WS).

**Streamer:** `SpeakFieldStreamer` must wait across chunks for incomplete `\uXXXX` / trailing `\` so split unicode escapes do not corrupt speak text.

Frontend listens via `applypilot:ws` + 5s status polling fallback (stop polling on start/submit failure).

## Frontend

- Entry: `ui/src/pages/mock-interview.ts` → `window.initMockInterviewTab(sessionId)`
- Modules: `ui/src/mock-interview/` (`api`, `voice`, `render`, `listeners`, `websocket`, `ws-guard`, `state`)
- Vite: `js/mock-interview.js` in `ui/vite.entries.json`
- `Permissions-Policy` must allow `microphone=(self)` in `main.py`
- UX matches Optimize CV: empty-state setup, config `<select>`s, AI Setup warning, `apply-decision-banner` session/results headers, `content-section` + `section-title`, `regen-btn` / `cl-copy-btn`
- If `active.status === complete` with `debrief`, render results even before history archive

